  <title>Convergence of Power Series (PS2)</title>
    <objectives>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <xi:include href="outcomes/02.ptx"/>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </objectives>
    
    <remark>
        <statement>
        <p>Consider a power series <m>\displaystyle\sum c_n(x-a)^n</m>.  Recall from <xref ref="fact-SQ7ratioTest"/> that if 
            <md>
                <mrow>\displaystyle \lim_{n\to \infty} \left|\frac{c_{n+1}(x-a)^{n+1}}{c_n(x-a)^n}\right| &amp; &lt; 1</mrow>
                <!--<mrow>\displaystyle \lim_{n\to \infty} \left|\frac{c_{n+1}(x-a)}{c_n}\right| &amp; &lt; 1</mrow>
                <mrow>\displaystyle \lim_{n\to \infty} |x-a|\left|\frac{c_{n+1}}{c_n}\right| &amp; &lt; 1</mrow>
                <mrow>\displaystyle |x-a|\lim_{n\to \infty} \left|\frac{c_{n+1}}{c_n}\right| &amp; &lt; 1</mrow>-->
            </md>
            then <m>\displaystyle\sum c_n(x-a)^n</m> converges.
        </p>
        
        <p>Then recall:
            <md>
                <mrow>\displaystyle \lim_{n\to \infty} \left|\frac{c_{n+1}(x-a)^{n+1}}{c_n(x-a)^n}\right| &amp; = \displaystyle \lim_{n\to \infty} \left|\frac{c_{n+1}(x-a)}{c_n}\right|</mrow>
                <mrow>&amp;=\displaystyle \lim_{n\to \infty} |x-a|\left|\frac{c_{n+1}}{c_n}\right| </mrow>
                <mrow>&amp;=\displaystyle |x-a|\lim_{n\to \infty} \left|\frac{c_{n+1}}{c_n}\right|. </mrow>
            </md>
        
        
        </p>
            
            </statement>
    </remark>
    
    
    <activity>
        <introduction>
            <p>
                Consider <m>\displaystyle\sum_{n=0}^\infty \frac{1}{n^2+1}x^n.</m>
            </p>
        </introduction>
        <task>
            <p>
                Letting <m>c_n=\frac{1}{n^2+1}</m> find <m>\displaystyle \lim_{n\to \infty} \left|\frac{c_{n+1}}{c_n}\right|</m>.
            </p>
            
        </task>
        
        <task>
            <p>
                For what values of <m>x</m> is <m>\displaystyle |x|\lim_{n\to \infty} \left|\frac{c_{n+1}}{c_n}\right| &lt; 1</m>?
                <ol marker="A">
                    <li><m>x &lt; 1</m>.</li>
                    <li><m>0\leq x &lt; 1</m>.</li>
                    <li><m>-1 &lt; x &lt; 1</m>.</li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </task>
        
        <task>
            <p>
                If <m>x=1</m>, does <m>\displaystyle\sum_{n=0}^\infty \frac{1}{n^2+1}x^n</m> converge?
            </p>
        </task>
        
        <task>
            <p>
                If <m>x=-1</m>, does <m>\displaystyle\sum_{n=0}^\infty \frac{1}{n^2+1}x^n</m> converge?
            </p>
        </task>
        
        
         <task>
            <p>
                Which of the following describe the values of <m>x</m> for which <m>\displaystyle\sum_{n=0}^\infty \frac{1}{n^2+1}x^n</m> converges?
                <ol marker="A">
                    <li><m>(-1,1)</m>.</li>
                    <li><m>[-1,1)</m>.</li>
                    <li><m>(-1,1]</m>.</li>
                    <li><m>[-1,1]</m>.</li>
                </ol>
